    $d A a f $.  $d A a w z $.  $d F a f $.  $d F a x y $.  $d X a f $.
    $d X a x y $.  $d a v x y $.  $d w x y z $.
    $( Extract a sequence ` f ` in ` X ` such that the image of the points in
       the bounded set ` A ` converges to the supremum ` S ` of the set.
       Similar to Equation 4 of [Kreyszig] p. 144.  (Contributed by Mario
       Carneiro, 15-Feb-2013.) $)
    supcvg $p |- ( ( ( X =/= (/) /\ F : X -onto-> A ) /\
       ( A C_ RR /\ E. z e. RR A. w e. A w <_ z ) ) ->
         E. f ( f : NN --> X /\ ( F o. f ) ~~> sup ( A , RR , < ) ) ) $=
      ( va vx vv vy wa cr cv cle wbr wral wrex cn co cvv wcel c0 wne wfo wss wf
      ccom clt csup cli wex reex ssex ad2antrl wi wceq foeq3 anbi2d sseq1 raleq
      rexbidv anbi12d supeq1 breq2d exbidv imbi12d cdiv cmin cmpt cfv crab eqid
      c1 weq opreq2 opreq2d cbvmptv breq2 ralbidv anbi2i supcvglem vtoclg mpcom
      cbvrexv ) CUAUBZFUCUDZFCEUEZLZCMUFZBNZANZOPZBCQZAMRZLZLZSFDNZUGZEWRUHZCMU
      IUJZUKPZLZDULZWJWFWIWOCMUMUNUOWGFHNZEUEZLZXEMUFZWMBXEQZAMRZLZLZWSWTXEMUIU
